text: Leptosteges parthenialis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Harrison Gray Dyar Jr. in 1917. It has been recorded from the US states of Florida, Louisiana and Oklahoma. The wingspan is about 13 mm. Adults have been recorded on wing from May to August.Moth Photographers Group at Mississippi State University ==References== Category:Moths described in 1917 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Leptosteges parthenialis
